----
Client-side pre-confirm updates/animations that should happen:
 * universal: "money" means current player, bank, and possibly other players (Purchase)
 * Draw
   * warn "this will trigger end game" as needed
 * TakeTruckPlaceTiles
   * if a placement creates an offspring, show it
   * if a placement completes an enclosure, show money bonus
   * coin tiles should animate off and update money
 * Move
   * update money
   * if offspring, show
   * if enclsoure completed, update money includes that bonus
 * Exchange
   * update money
   * (no completion bonus possible)
   * if offspring, show
 * Discard tile
    * update money cost
    * (no offspring possible)
 * Purchase tile
    * update money
    * if complete enclosure, update money includes that
    * (no offspring possible)
 * Expand zoo
    * update money

Open question is how to deal with "restart". (and probably, eventually undo).
Right now we keep track of animations and replay them backwards. We could instead keep track of Promises to evaluate (where some are animations). (Leverage Counter::getValue to get money undos; offspring undos are just animations).